      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The squealing noise from your 2018 Toyota Camry, a classic case of a brake pad warning sign, rather like a goblin's warning signal when it's time to scurry for cover. You see, when the brake pads are worn down, they can cause the caliper to rub against the rotor, producing that high-pitched squeal. It's a bit like a goblin's warning shout, \"Danger, danger, danger!\" - you'd better check those brake pads pronto!\n\nNow, let's get down to business. To diagnose the issue, I'd recommend checking the brake pads and rotors for wear. If they're worn down, it's likely that the squeal will continue to occur. You can also check the brake fluid level and condition, as low or dirty fluid can cause the brake pads to wear down faster. It's a bit like a goblin's favorite trick - making you think everything is fine when it's not.\n\nIf you're not comfortable with DIY brake pad replacements, it's always best to consult a professional mechanic. They'll be able to assess the situation and provide a proper diagnosis and repair. After all, you don't want to be stuck with a squealing brake pad, that",
